<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-568-142  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 568 142.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 11 1990 v4 n23 p16(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OFPP to suggest buying reg changes: expected to reconcile BuyAmerican, Trade Agreement acts. (Office of Federal ProcurementPolicy; regulation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kellner, Mark A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A year-long study by the Office of Federal Procurement Policy ofthe effects of the Buy American and Trade Agreement acts onfederal buying will culminate in the release of a report that isexpected to suggest changes in the regulations governinggovernment data processing spending, including spending onmicrocomputers.andP;  Current regulations require that any unit bid fora federal contract must consist of more than 50 percent US-madeparts for any contract under $172,000.andP;  Over that level there isno percentage required, but the country involved must be a TradeAgreements Act signatory.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Government RegulationRegulationTradePurchasing SystemsUnited States. Office of Federal Procurement Policy.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>